        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 12:45PM CDT by NWS Lake Charles LA</headline>
        <description>At 1245 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Clifton, or 11 miles northwest of Hineston, moving northeast at 50
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to vegetation and outdoor
objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Boyce, Lena, Slagle, Lacamp, Leander, Sieper, Hutton, Clifton,
Flatwoods, and Simpson.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
